Usage:
  cape test [options]

Description:
  Runs the complete UPLC CAPE test suite to verify all CLI commands and 
  scripts work correctly. This includes testing benchmark creation, 
  submission management, file validation, and integration workflows.

Options:
  -h, --help    Show this help message

Examples:
  cape test           # Run full test suite
  cape test --help    # Show this help

The test suite runs in a sandboxed environment and does not modify your
actual project files. It tests:
- CAPE CLI functionality (benchmark, submission commands)
- Template-based file creation
- Input validation and error conditions
- Integration workflows
- Directory structure validation

Note: This command must be run from within the nix development shell.